			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">mode 0 is a good idea.  shm_unlink before ftruncate is reasonable too, but only 
narrows the timing window for the race.  essentially the racer has to do chmod in the 
/dev/shm/ subtree and then shm_open, all between the shm_open and shm_unlink.  given 
we're defending against somebody who can execute as the same uid as us, they could 
just as well ptrace us.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-03-03T05:20:08.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-03-03T05:20:08.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 7 by b...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=240#c7" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/240/comments/full/7" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>